post_text:
K-2 Star Students of the Week! ¡Estudiantes de K-2 Star de la semana!¡ 💫🌟💫🌟

These six students showed #Community all week long! Community means we help each other because we are stronger together. Congratulations!!!!!! #successatmarshall #pride #integrity #perseverance #integrity #courage #curiosity

Shown clockwise from the left: Jaycian (2nd-grade), Da’shawn (Kindergarten), Joel (1st-grade), and Deyma (1st-grade). Not pictured (but not forgotten!), Byron (2nd-grade), and Genesis (Kindergarten).

¡Estudiantes de K-2 Star de la semana! ¡Estos seis estudiantes mostraron #Comunidad durante toda la semana! Comunidad significa que nos ayudamos unos a otros porque juntos somos más fuertes. ¡¡¡¡¡¡Felicidades!!!!!! #successatmarshall #orgullo #integridad # perseverancia #integridad #coraje #curiosidad

Se muestra en el sentido de las agujas del reloj desde la izquierda: Jaycian (segundo grado), Da’shawn (jardín de infantes), Joel (primer grado) y Deyma (primer grado). No en la foto (¡pero no olvidado!), Byron (segundo grado) y Genesis (jardín de infantes).

¡Familias!

Nos complace anunciar que las clases se reanudarán, a través del aprendizaje a distancia, mañana a las 8:30. ¡Por favor asegúrese de que su estudiante se ponga al día con cualquier trabajo faltante y comuníquese con su asesor si necesita ayuda!

Families!

We are pleased to announce that classes will resume, through Distance Learning, tomorrow at 8:30. Please make sure your student catches up on any missing work and reaches out to their advisor if they need help!

post_text: City of NOLA meal programs have been extended! The quickest way to register is online at: nola311.org/MealAssist or residents can call 3-1-1. La forma más rápida de registrarse es en línea en: nola311.org/MealAssist o los residentes pueden llamar al 3-1-1. Se recomienda a las personas que no hablan inglés que llamen al 3-1-1 para obtener ayuda para solicitar el programa.

Families: All students will start the 2020-2021 school year with Distance Learning. We will be contacting student families with more information this week! Stay healthy and safe!
shared_text:
Orleans Parish School Board
July 21 at 1:40 PM ·

*Important Update* While we believe it’s absolutely critical to get students back into the classroom, the latest data is going in the wrong direction, telling us we just can’t do so at this time. That’s why, we’re announcing that all students will start the school year with #distancelearning in August, with a goal of getting students back to in-person after Labor Day. #NOLAed #NOLAPSTogether #MaskUpNOLA
#schoolreopening

shared_text:
Orleans Parish School Board
May 18 at 10:09 AM ·

Attention NOLA-PS families: Citywide Community Feeding schedule will be slightly altered this week due to Memorial Day holiday on Monday, May 25th.

Today (May 18), families will be able to pick-up meals for 2 days
Wednesday (May 20), families will be able to pick-up meals for 2 days

post_text: Operation Spark just announced that online coding camp registration is open! Sign your student up today! #oneapp413 #successatmarshall #community #curiosity #integrity
shared_text:
DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
Operation Spark - Online "Hour of Code" - Grades 4 to 8 - Application

Operation Spark
April 2 at 9:50 AM ·

Operation Spark is excited to begin offering a daily live, online "hour of code" to students in grades 4-8 attending any Orleans Parish public school. Students will be introduced to design thinking and basic coding concepts through the use of Scratch, a free visual coding language developed by MIT Media Lab. Operation Spark's full-time instructional staff has been teaching live online classes to high school students across the state for two years, and are excited to lend their expertise to younger students navigating online learning.

The course will meet Monday through Friday, 11 AM to 12 PM, starting April 6, for two weeks. The minimum tech requirements are a laptop, desktop, or Chromebook and a stable internet connection.

Visit https://bit.ly/opsparkhourofcode to apply.

Orleans Parish School Board
April 2 at 5:56 PM ·

Per today’s announcement by Governor John Bel Edwards to extend the stay-at-home order through April 30th, all NOLA public schools will remain closed for the duration of the month of April. This necessary action is an effective way to slow the spread of COVID-19 across our city and state.

Learn more: https://nolapublicschools.com/news/press-releases/nola-public-schools-announces-districtwide-school-closures-extension-through-april-30-due-to-covid-19-health-crisis
